{{Quote|We must not repeat the mistakes of the past.|A Jedi Historian|<ref name="Threat of the Conqueror">{{SWGTCG|set=Threat of the Conqueror|cardname=Jedi Historian}}</ref>}}
'''Jedi historians''', also called '''Jedi chroniclers''', were members of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] who had chosen to pursue the teachings of the [[Jedi Consular|Consular]], specializing as a [[Lore Keeper]]. These Jedi were dedicated to researching the history of the Jedi Order.

==Overview==
As a Lore Keeper, a Jedi could specialize in one or more of three sub-branches: the [[Jedi archivist/Legends|Jedi archivist]], [[Jedi librarian/Legends|Jedi librarian]], or Jedi historian. While all Lore Keepers made up the [[Librarian's Assembly]] at the [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]], historians were charged with specifically analyzing the history of eras past, which included the history of the Order. Not restricted to Coruscant historians were often assigned to satellite training facilities, most notably the academies of [[Kamparas Jedi Training Center|Kamparas]], [[Telosian Jedi Academy|Telos]], and [[Obroa-skai/Legends|Obroa-skai]].<ref name="TJP" />

Historians were at their greatest numbers when times were relatively peaceful; during war time, the [[Jedi Council/Legends|Jedi Councils]] need as many Jedi in the field as possible, reducing the numbers that could stay within the academies. During the height of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], large groups of these Jedi would meet to discuss and analyze their most recent theories and findings. Many historians traveled to the fringes of civilized space with the [[Exploration Corps/Legends|Exploration Corps]] to study newly discovered space and uncover lost and forgotten artifacts like [[Holocron/Legends|holocrons]] and fragments of historic writings. Additionally, the [[Council of First Knowledge/Legends|Council of First Knowledge]] was made up of Jedi historians, and advised on matters requiring the use of ancient Jedi lore.<ref name="TJP" />

While most historians opted for the traditional set of [[Jedi apparel/Legends|robes]] of the Order, a set of robes with [[Ansata pattern/Legends|Ansata patterns]] on them saw use by some of the most prominent historians of the Old Republic, such as Masters [[Atris]]<ref name="KOTORII">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]''</ref> and [[Jocasta Nu/Legends|Jocasta Nu]].<ref name="AOTC">{{Film|II}}</ref> [[Tionne Solusar]] would revive the design following the [[New Jedi Order|resurrection]] of the Order after the [[Great Jedi Purge/Legends|Great Jedi Purge]].<ref name="JVS">[[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']]</ref>

==Known historians of the Old Jedi Order==
[[File:ControlTheForce-TSS.png|thumb|left|200px|[[Rachi Sitra]] was a Jedi historian seeking to uncover forgotten knowledge]]
While many historians existed over the history of the Order, only a few names have survived the passage of time. It is known that during the [[Jedi Civil War]], Master [[Dorak]] served as Chronicler at the [[Jedi Enclave|enclave]] on [[Dantooine/Legends|Dantooine]], as well as sitting on the [[Dantooine Jedi Enclave Council|Council]] there. Dorak was in the process of training his apprentice, [[Deesra Luur Jada]], to secede him as Chronicler, but he was killed in the [[Conclave at Katarr|Devastation of Katarr]] before he could complete Jada's training. The [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] however managed to complete his training and help recover some valuable data throughout the rest of the war.<ref name="KOTOR">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''</ref>

During the same period, Master [[Kreia]] served as a historian at the Coruscant Temple under [[Lore Keeper|Chief Librarian]] [[Atris]]. Aside from her duties on the High Council and in the Archives, Atris was responsible for the construction of the [[Telosian Jedi Academy|input locks]] on [[Telos IV]] where she secretly stored stolen holocrons for safe-keeping. One of her [[Echani/Legends|Echani]] [[Handmaiden/Legends|handmaidens]] [[Brianna]], would succeed her in caring for the Telosian Academy, making sure the knowledge stayed within the control of the Order.<ref name="KOTORII" />

Following the [[Great Galactic War]] and the [[Sacking of Coruscant]], the Order lost the Archives within the Temple and was forced to rebuild on [[Tython/Legends|Tython]]. The High Council placed Master [[Gnost-Dural]] in charge of the reconstruction of the databanks, creating an updated timeline of the events preceding the outbreak of war.<ref name="Timeline 1: Treaty of Coruscant">{{TORweb|url=holonet/galactic-history|text=Timeline 1: Treaty of Coruscant|int=Timeline 1: Treaty of Coruscant}}</ref> Several centuries later following the [[Ruusan Reformations/Legends|Ruusan Reformations]] of the Republic, Chief Librarian and [[Caretaker of First Knowledge/Legends|Caretaker of First Knowledge]] [[Restelly Quist/Legends|Restelly Quist]] was a historian responsible for refocusing the teachings of the academy. During the [[Golden Age of the Old Republic]], the role of historian was filled by many, including Master [[Thame Cerulian]], a [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] with an interest in the study of the inner workings of the [[Sith holocron/Legends|Sith holocrons]] stored in the [[Holocron Vault/Legends|Holocron Vaults]].<ref name="TJP" /> Masters [[Tahl]] and [[Rachi Sitra]] were some of the last historians of the Order, with Master Sitra surviving well into the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="Threat of the Conqueror" /> The last of the Chief Librarians was Master [[Jocasta Nu/Legends|Jocasta Nu]], who would govern the Archives for thirty years before dying among her beloved books during [[Operation: Knightfall/Legends|Operation: Knightfall]].<ref name="Episode III">[[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith (video game)|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'' video game]]</ref>

